Magento 2.4.6-p7 to 2.4.8-p5 Upgrade - Complete Command Overview
1. Pre-Upgrade Commands

# Check Magento version
php bin/magento --version

# Check PHP version
php -v

# Check Composer version
composer --version

# Check OpenSearch/Elasticsearch
curl -X GET "localhost:9200/_cluster/health?pretty"

2. Backup Commands
# Quick code backup (excluding heavy files)
tar -czf magento_core_backup_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).tar.gz \
  --exclude='pub/media/catalog/product/cache' \
  --exclude='pub/media/cache' \
  --exclude='var/cache' \
  --exclude='var/page_cache' \
  --exclude='var/session' \
  --exclude='var/log' \
  --exclude='*.zip' \
  --exclude='*.gz' \
  --exclude='vendor/*/test' \
  --exclude='vendor/*/tests' \
  app bin lib pub var vendor composer.json

# Database backup
mysqldump -u [username] -p[password] [database] --single-transaction --quick --skip-lock-tables | gzip > db_backup_$(date +%Y%m%d_%H%M%S).sql.gz

# Backup composer files
cp composer.json composer.json.backup
cp composer.lock composer.lock.backup

3. Enable Maintenance Mode
php bin/magento maintenance:enable

Composer Update Commands
4. Update Composer
# Update composer itself
composer self-update

# Clear composer cache
composer clear-cache

5. Update Magento Version
# Use require-commerce for Magento 2.4.6+
composer require-commerce magento/product-community-edition 2.4.8-p5 --no-update

# OR manual edit composer.json
nano composer.json
# Change: "magento/product-community-edition": "2.4.6-p7" 
# To: "magento/product-community-edition": "2.4.8-p5"

6. Update Dependencies
# Full update with all dependencies
composer update --with-all-dependencies

# If PHP version issues
composer update --ignore-platform-req=php

# With increased memory
php -d memory_limit=8G /usr/local/bin/composer update

7. Fix Symfony Version Conflicts
# Update Symfony packages to 6.4
composer require symfony/process:^6.4 symfony/finder:^6.4 symfony/console:^6.4 symfony/config:^6.4 symfony/dependency-injection:^6.4 --with-all-dependencies

8. Fix Specific Package Conflicts
# Update PHPUnit
composer require phpunit/phpunit:^9.6 --no-update

# Update testing framework
composer require magento/magento2-functional-testing-framework:^4.4 --dev --no-update

# Update PHP CS Fixer
composer require friendsofphp/php-cs-fixer:^3.50 --dev --no-update

# Remove problematic packages
composer remove phpmd/phpmd pdepend/pdepend sebastian/phpcpd --dev --no-update


9.  Database Upgrade Commands
# Main upgrade command
php bin/magento setup:upgrade

# With increased memory
php -d memory_limit=8G bin/magento setup:upgrade

# With safe mode
php -d memory_limit=8G bin/magento setup:upgrade --safe-mode --no-interaction

# With verbose output
php bin/magento setup:upgrade --verbose

# Separate schema and data upgrade
php bin/magento setup:db-schema:upgrade --no-interaction
php bin/magento setup:db-data:upgrade --no-interaction

10.  Fix Stuck Upgrade
# Remove database locks
mysql -u [username] -p[password] -e "DELETE FROM [database].flag WHERE flag_code='setup_upgrade_lock';"

# Kill stuck process
ps aux | grep "setup:upgrade"
sudo kill -9 [PID]

# Clean and retry
rm -rf generated/* var/di/* var/generation/* var/cache/*
php bin/magento cache:flush
php -d memory_limit=8G bin/magento setup:upgrade --safe-mode --no-interaction

Static Content Deployment

11. Deploy Static Content
# Deploy with compact strategy
php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy -f --strategy=compact nl_NL

# Deploy with standard strategy
php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy -f --strategy=standard nl_NL

# Deploy all locales
php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy -f --strategy=compact en_US en_GB de_DE fr_FR es_ES nl_NL

# Deploy specific theme only
php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy -f --strategy=compact --theme=Smartwave/indeshop nl_NL

# Deploy with multiple jobs
php bin/magento setup:static-content:deploy -f --strategy=compact --jobs=4 nl_NL


